Hi all,

Some of you might notice a slowdown of your system when using the Blitz 
debugger and a graphics card (or UAE, happens to me in window mode).

This is due to some combinations of graphics subsystem and card, as not all 
support hardware interrupts on vertical blanks. Consequently, WaitTOF_ isn't 
always a good solution to use on graphics cards. Unfortunately, the REDDebugger 
uses this to cause a delay in it's main loop. I've disassembled it (oops :) and 
changed this to Delay_(3), which helps a lot.

Anyone who wants it, go to http://members.nbci.com/david_mcminn/blitz2.html 
(near the bottom of the page) and read the readme for full instructions.


