Hi twill@...

> At  the  end  of  my  programmcode i incbin some datas...  When i start the
> executeable file, my datas will all be in ChipMem ;( !  Is there any way to put 
> IncBin  stuff (by starting the executeable) automatical to FastMem (if FastMem
> is available) instead of ChipMem!!!  Because this datas must not be in ChipMem
> like Gfx/Snd i.e.!!

If there is fastmem available on your computer, AmigaDOS will load the program 
into fastmem - so all the data will be in fastmem also.

This is because Blitz creates executables with a single ADOS hunk in it, and 
AFAIK it never sets the bit for specifying this hunk must be loaded into 
chipmem.

On a more general point, there is no way to control the hunk memory types in 
Blitz (and there is only ever 1 hunk anyway, although I think you can add a 
debug hunk to it) like you can in some C compilers with things like __chip etc.


