The gvpscsi2.device boards ( most G-Forces) are limited in their
controllers. They will only allocate 32K of memory for the filesystems, and
as PFS2/3, SFS, AFS etc are all larger than that, their isn't enough memory
to start the filesystem. Basically, you cannot run any modern filesystems on
these boards. I think the Guru ROM cured this on the early boards, but the
G-Force doesn't have the same type of ROM. Tough shit :)
  
