Yep, it's just a block of memory, but the size of the newtype is rounded
up to the nearest even number of bytes.

So if you have:

    NEWTYPE.blah
      a.w
      b.s
    END NEWTYPE

    Dim blah2.blah(10)

You can do:

    *ptr.blah = &blah2(0)
    ; Process some stuff
    *ptr = *ptr + ((Sizeof.blah + 1) AND $FFFFFFFE)

