Well, if you don't/can't/won't use some of the pre-existing commands, as Tony 
suggested, you can do this to get pointers to list items:

; Fill in list here
If FirstItem(listname())
    *ln.Node = &listname() - 8
    *lst.List = *ln\ln_Pred
Else
    *lst.List = 0
End If

And now you can do anything you want really, using normal list things. Check 
what the value of *lst is though, because if it's zero, there are no items so 
you wouldn't bother sorting.

Oh, and rather than use the bubble sort, don't swap at every opportunity. Find 
the highest and lowest and then swap them at the end of the iteration. Then, 
search in the remaining unsorted items. Francis Loch told me about that, very 
useful (faster).

